during 2004, the company initiated purchases of shares under the $2,000 share buyback plan authorized by the board of directors in june2001. as of december31,
2004, 10.6million shares at a cost of $457 were purchased under this program. management has not established a timeline for the buyback of the remaining stock under this plan.
in
2002, the company completed the purchase and retirement of shares under the $2,500 share buyback program previously approved by the board of directors. purchases of 10.8million shares for
$470 were made in 2002.
